  "metadata": {
    "fn_id": "pacific_island_contest",
    "note": "Terrain gate = the island centroids (MELANESIA/POLYNESIA/MICRONESIA/PNG); bundle carries the PHENOMENON only. NO island toponyms: the centroid already locates the geography, and aliases are OR'd -- a bare `Fiji` would admit every cyclone/rugby/tourism title (measured ~63% on-topic). No `Australia`/`China` (country names, handled by centroids on the dyad atomics). No `police` (PNG domestic crime noise) -- only the named `policing initiative`. Verbs are safe here because the island centroid is a tight terrain gate (562 titles/180d).\n\nThe 'Military signalling' term was DROPPED after the first audit: its generic war vocabulary (`ballistic missile`/`warship`, and the ja/zh equivalents) is a spec-3 leak class, and it was pulling Japanese Iran/Israel coverage in through the OCEANIA-PAPUANEWGUINEA centroid bug (`ラエ` = Lae, a substring of `イスラエル`). The Pacific missile-test titles are NOT lost -- they all carry ASIA-CHINA + OCEANIA-AUSTRALIA and are held by china_threat_assessment, which is where the military-reach phenomenon lives. This atomic is the diplomatic/security-alignment contest; that split is orthogonal."
  },
